

How to create a local Git repository and start tracking changes?
1. Navigate to your project folder with cd command
   cd C:\Users\Username\Desktop\Project
2. Intialize a git repository
   git init
3. Add files to the staging area
   git add . -> adds all files
   git add <fileName> -> adds a specific file
4. Commit the changes in Staging area
   git commit -m "commit message"
5. Check the status at any point
   git status
6. Check the commit log 
   git log
   git log --pretty=oneline
   git log -p               
How to push a local repository to a remote?
1. Create a remote repo
2. Connect the local repostory with the remote
   git remote add <nameOfRemoteRepo> <urlToRemoteRepo>
   git remote add origin https://github.com/dtacademyb11/Demo.git
3. Rename the remote main branch name  
   git branch -M main
4. Push the changes
   git push -u origin main (authorization must be done if it is the first time you are pushing to this remote repo)
   every subsequent push is done with 'git push'